Two-database architecture
=========================

- ``projects.db`` (shared metadata) — schema evolution managed by Alembic.
- Per-project ``graph.db`` — managed at runtime by
  ``GraphBase.metadata.create_all(engine)`` inside ``DatabaseManager``.

Development bootstrap
---------------------

During development, ``DatabaseManager.__init__`` calls
``ProjectsBase.metadata.create_all()`` to bootstrap ``projects.db``
without requiring a migration run.  This is a convenience so a fresh
checkout works immediately.

Once the schema stabilises, generate and run an Alembic migration::

    alembic upgrade head
    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"

In production the recommended path is to deploy via Alembic migrations
rather than relying on ``create_all`` (which cannot detect schema drift
or apply incremental changes).  The ``create_all`` call is idempotent
(``CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS``) and will not overwrite an existing,
up-to-date database, so running both is harmless.

Usage
-----

Default (projects.db)::

    alembic upgrade head
    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "..."

Graph schema (for schema design / migration authoring)::

    alembic -x db=graph revision --autogenerate -m "..."
    alembic -x db=graph upgrade head

The URL in ``alembic.ini`` is a fallback; the real URL is built
dynamically in ``env.py`` with ``~`` expansion and directory creation.
